gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Mavericks 123, Kings 119
gameRecap.excerpt: Kyrie Irving recorded 31 points (19 points, 9-11 FG in the 4th quarter) and 8 assists for the Mavericks as they overcame a 13-point deficit and defeated the Kings, 123-119. Luka Doncic added 29 points, 10 rebounds, and 6 assists for the Mavericks in the victory, while De’Aaron Fox (28 points, 8 assists) and Domantas Sabonis (19 points, 11 rebounds, 11 assists) combined for 47 points for the Kings in the losing effort. The Mavericks improve to 38-42 on the season, while the Kings fall to 48-32.
